### LOGIN - Get JWT Token (Use this first!)
POST http://localhost:8080/plataforma/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "username": "admin",
  "password": "123"
}

# Response will be a JWT token string like: "eyJhbGciOiJIUzM4NCJ9..."
# Copy this token and use it in the Authorization header for other requests

### Get authenticated user (replace <JWT_TOKEN> with the token returned above)
GET http://localhost:8080/academics/api/auth/user
Accept: application/json
Authorization: Bearer eyJhbGciOiJIUzM4NCJ9.eyJzdWIiOiJhZG1pbiIsImlhdCI6MTc2NzQ1MjMzNCwiZXhwIjoxNzY3NDU1OTM0fQ.qvflgzxJ-iMRjUgFOx_s4qOSIfRRP5vV0ZsRvTTCyQb40JuMvcWNhEipVoivubqO



